## What to do
Create three immutable model classes. These are pure data classes — no business logic, no Supabase, no JSON serialization yet.

### Class: `UserModel` (lib/models/user_model.dart)
```dart
class UserModel {
  final String id;
  final String name;
  final String apartment; // e.g. "Depto 3A"
  const UserModel({required this.id, required this.name, required this.apartment});
}
```

### Class: `CleaningSchedule` (lib/models/cleaning_schedule.dart)
```dart
class CleaningSchedule {
  final String id;
  final String userId;
  final DateTime date;
  final bool isCompleted;
  const CleaningSchedule({required this.id, required this.userId, required this.date, this.isCompleted = false});
}
```

### Class: `CleaningTask` (lib/models/cleaning_task.dart)
Represents one checklist item in a cleaning session.
```dart
class CleaningTask {
  final String id;
  final String scheduleId;
  final String title;
  final bool isCompleted;
  const CleaningTask({required this.id, required this.scheduleId, required this.title, this.isCompleted = false});

  CleaningTask copyWith({bool? isCompleted}) => CleaningTask(
    id: id, scheduleId: scheduleId, title: title,
    isCompleted: isCompleted ?? this.isCompleted,
  );
}
```

The 8 default task titles (in Spanish) are:
1. Lavar el retrete
2. Lavar el lavamanos
3. Lavar la regadera
4. Barrer
5. Trapear
6. Secar el piso
7. Sacar la basura
8. Limpiar las jergas

These titles will be used by the mock data provider, NOT stored as constants in the model file.

## Do not
- Add JSON serialization (fromJson/toJson) — that is future backend work
- Import anything except dart:core (no flutter imports needed)
- Add any business logic or validation
- Store the default task titles list in these files

